{"lemma":"مِقْلادِ","slug":"مِقْلادِ","root":"ق.ل.د","root_slug":"ق-ل-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ل-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36135"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%82%D9%92%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"key","examples":[{"text":"لَهُ مَقَالِيدُ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْأَرْضِ يَبْسُطُ الرِّزْقَ لِمَن يَشَاءُ وَيَقْدِرُ إِنَّهُ بِكُلِّ شَيْءٍ عَلِيمٌ","english":"To Him pertain the keys of the heavens and the earth. He extends provision for whom He wills and restricts [it]. Indeed He is of all things knowing."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"switch","examples":[{"text":"أَغْلَقَ/فَتَحَ مِقْلَادًا وَشَغَّلَ/أَوْقَفَ الْجِهَازَ"},{"text":"يَسْمَحُ مِقْلَادٌ بِمُرُورِ التَّيَّارِ الْكَهْرَبَائِيِّ عِنْدَ إِغْلَاقِهِ وَيَمْنَعُ الْمُرُورَ عِنْدَ فَتْحِهِ","english":"A switch allows the passage of electric current when it is turned on and prevents its passage when it is turned off."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun derivative of إِقْلِيد (ʔiqlīd, “key”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36135","headword_ar":"مِقْلَادٌ","root":"qld","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A repository, magazine, store-room,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treasury;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qil~iydN","text_ar":"قِلِّيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAliydu","text_ar":"مَقَالِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqoliydN","text_ar":"اـِقْلِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}